## M11: qualified enum access (`Color.red`).
##
## Same as `.red` but written explicitly with the enum name. Sema
## type-checks the variant exists and lowers naturally to Zig's
## `Color.red` syntax.
##
## EXPECTED: clean. Runs and prints `.red`.

enum Color
  red
  green
  blue

sub main()
  c: Color = Color.red
  print(c)
